An uncleaned find is a rock obtained in the Varrock Museum specimen cleaning activity. Players need to use it on a specimen table to reveal the archaeological artefact inside (see the list below). The cleaning activity can be done after finishing The Dig Site quest.

Players can take part in the cleaning activity in the south fenced-off corner of the museum. The tools necessary to do so can be found in the tool rack hanging on the wall. Players can then show the artefact to one of the archaeologists in the room, who will then tell them what to do with the item. Certain items are eligible for being displayed in the display cases. Other items can be put in the storage crates. On average, this results in 3-5 antique lamps per hour, depending on your efficiency.

Items[edit | edit source]

Note that sometimes, you accidentally destroy the find, resulting in the following message: The find crumbles to dust in your hands - oops! Better not let the professionals see that one!

The following items can be found by cleaning:

Item Uses
Pottery Players should place it in display case 22 for a one-time reward of 10 kudos.

Players can put it in the storage crate to get one of the rewards listed in the table below.

Old symbol Players should place it in display case 36 for a one-time reward of 10 kudos.
Ancient symbol Players should place it in display case 37 for a one-time reward of 10 kudos.
Old coin Players should place it in display case 45 for a one-time reward of 10 kudos.
Ancient coin Players should place it in display case 44 for a one-time reward of 10 kudos.
Clean necklace It is obtained at a rate of 1/51.[1]

After finding it, players must then talk to one of the archaeologists cleaning finds in the museum. They will teach the player how to enchant a ruby necklace to make a Digsite pendant, and they will then remove the clean necklace from the player's inventory. It cannot be obtained again after this happens. The necklace may be worn, although it has the same appearance as a ruby necklace.

Jewellery Players can show it to one of the six archaeologists in the room to receive 5 coins.

Players can put it in the storage crate to get one of the rewards listed in the table below.

Old chipped vase Players can put it in the storage crate to get one of the rewards listed in the table below.
Arrowheads Players can put it in the storage crate to get one of the rewards listed in the table below.
Broken arrow Broken arrows can be repaired at a repair bench in a player-owned house.
Broken glass It is used during a few quests. The broken glass cannot be added to the storage crate when adding finds.
Iron dagger A melee weapon that can be used in combat.
Uncut opal Uncut opals can be cut with a chisel resulting in an opal or a crushed gem.
Uncut jade Uncut jades can be cut with a chisel resulting in a jade or a crushed gem.
Bones Bones give 4.5 Prayer experience when buried.
Coins The most common form of currency in Gielinor.

You will receive approximately 2/3rds of your uncleaned finds as any combination of pottery, jewellery, old chipped vases and arrowheads.

By adding these items into the Storage crates you'll receive in exchange one of the following:
